Berkshire Hathaway Energy

666 Grand Ave.Ste. 500 P.O. Box 657
Des Moines IA 50306 United States
Phone: +1 515-___-____
Fax: +1 515-___-____
https://www.berkshirehathawayenergyco.com





44
Managers




311
IT employees




$667.5MEST.
IT Budget




Berkshire Hathaway Energy is an energy production and distribution company that operates through its subsidiaries MidAmerican Energy Company, PacifiCorp, CE Electric UK, CalEnergy Generation, Kern River Gas Transmission Company and Northern Natural Gas.

Berkshire Hathaway Energy acquired NV Energy in December,… MoreBerkshire Hathaway Energy is an energy production and distribution company that operates through its subsidiaries MidAmerican Energy Company, PacifiCorp, CE Electric UK, CalEnergy Generation, Kern River Gas Transmission Company and Northern Natural Gas.

Berkshire Hathaway Energy acquired NV Energy in December, 2013.  NV Energy is profiled separately on this database.
Berkshire Hathaway Energy is an energy production and distribution company that operates through its subsidiaries MidAmerican Energy Company, PacifiCorp, CE Electric UK, CalEnergy Generation, Kern River Gas Transmission Company and Northern Natural Gas.

Berkshire Hathaway Energy acquired NV Energy in December,… MoreBerkshire Hathaway Energy is an energy production and distribution company that operates through its subsidiaries MidAmerican Energy Company, PacifiCorp, CE Electric UK, CalEnergy Generation, Kern River Gas Transmission Company and Northern Natural Gas.

Berkshire Hathaway Energy acquired NV Energy in December, 2013.  NV Energy is profiled separately on this database.

IT Priorities:
• Plans to increase spending in cloud hosting and virtualization, and decrease spending in outsourcing and staffing.

IT Structure:
• Berkshire Hathaway Energy Company's IT is largely decentralized with individual business unit CIOs having responsibility for their respective units.
• PacifiCorp, a subsidiary based in Portland, OR, maintains a large IT department.
• Kern River Gas Transmission, a subsidiary based in Salt Lake City, UT, has a small IT staff overseeing Infrastructure, and Systems.
• Northern Natural Gas, a subsidiary based in Omaha, NE, maintains a small IT department.

IT Intelligence:
• Avoiding a bring your own device (BYOD) policy due to the lack of simpliciy in managing a large-scale and enterprise-wide program.
• No longer looking into cloud storage solutions due to security on an enterprise level.

2012:
• Focusing on the development of business applications using Oracle and Visio.
• Virtualizing its server environment with VMware and other virtualization technologies.
• Plans to increase spending in infrastructure and storage.





